The paper discusses the design and optimization of content distribution networks (CDNs) for video streaming systems, which involves network infrastructure, multimedia processing, and system optimization. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also discusses the optimization of video streaming quality, which falls under cs.MM (Multimedia). Additionally, the paper discusses the allocation of resources and optimization of system performance, which could fall under cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) and cs.SY (Systems and Control). Finally, the paper discusses the use of algorithms to optimize system performance, which could fall under cs.IT (Information Theory).
